-- New York Knicks’ Late Comeback Stalls in 95-85 Loss in Dallas to Mavericks
-- B y   R o b   G l o s t e r
-- 2012-03-07T04:06:22Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-07/new-york-knicks-late-comeback-stalls-in-95-85-loss-in-dallas-to-mavericks.html
A fourth-quarter comeback fell short
and the  New York Knicks  lost their third straight road game with
a 95-85 defeat at the  Dallas Mavericks .  The Knicks trailed 77-63 after three quarters before
opening the fourth period with a 15-0 run to take a one-point
lead.  Dallas’ Dirk Nowitzki then scored six straight points,
Jason Kidd hit a 3-pointer and Nowitzki hit another jumper to
highlight a 14-0 run as the Mavs rebuilt their lead.  Nowitzki finished with 28 points for Dallas (23-17), the
defending National Basketball Association champion. Amar’e
Stoudemire had 26 points for the Knicks (18-20), who have lost
five of their last eight games after going on a seven-game
winning streak with Jeremy Lin as their new point guard.  Lin had 14 points on 4-for-13 shooting and seven assists.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
